                                    <p>‘Fellowship in Critical Care’ is an intensive training program designed for medical professionals seeking to elevate their expertise in area of critical care medicine. This is a medical specialty that focuses on the management and treatment of patients with life-threatening illnesses or injuries. Practitioners in this field, known as critical care physicians or intensivists, are highly trained to provide specialized care to patients who require close monitoring, advanced life support, and complex medical interventions. Critical care is typically delivered in an intensive care unit (ICU) or critical care unit (CCU) within a hospital.</p>

